fields.Title: PLAZA ORB / neither man clicked
fields.Condition: (Variable["plaza.rene_or_gaston_have_clicked_on_petanquista_gaston_can_safely_spawn_on_bench"] == false  and  Variable["plaza.petanquista_gone_afterthought_done"] == false   and  IsDayFrom(5))  and  Variable["TASK.locate_ruby_on_the_coast_done"] == false  or  (Variable["TASK.locate_ruby_on_the_coast_done"] == true  and  Variable["TASK.report_to_the_tribunal_done"] == true)
fields.Description: An orb to appear on the fifth day (or after triubnal) and address the disappearance of the pétanquista, if the player hasn't talked to either of them.
fields.Placement: In and around the crater on the plaza where the old used to play petanque. Should extend outside a bit, so the player might get it when they run by.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "No need to beat yourself down over..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No need to beat yourself down over it. It probably wasn't the definitive piece of the puzzle. Still, somehow it feels like May bells matter somehow.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "The pétanque players?"
fields.Dialogue Text: The pétanque players?

fields.Title: You: ""Wait, maybe they died during the m..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wait, maybe they died during the mercenary tribunal?"
fields.Alternate1: Maybe they too died during the mercenary tribunal?

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""And, I mean... it would be one twi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "And, I mean... it would be one twist too many if it turned out these two old men were our killers. That's just unlikely. No..." He seems pleased with himself. "We would only have wasted our time here."

fields.Title: You: ""Damn, I missed asking these guys a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Damn, I missed asking these guys about the dried May bells."
fields.Alternate1: Damn. Looks like I missed asking these guys about the dried May bells.

fields.Title: You: ""But what if I wanted to talk to th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "But what if I wanted to talk to them?"

fields.Title: Empathy: "The lieutenant is thinking of all t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant is thinking of all the time you've spared. He likes it.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Awful lonely here. No ruckus. No ol..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Awful lonely here. No ruckus. No old men playing their little ball game.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "*Still* you can't shake the feeling..."
fields.Dialogue Text: *Still* you can't shake the feeling that somehow these may bell do actually matter. If only a little bit.

fields.Title: Logic: "It was probably nothing anyway. Jus..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It was probably nothing anyway. Just a little thought you had.

fields.Title: You: "Yeah, where did they go?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Yeah, where did they go?

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""They didn't," the lieutenant calms..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "They didn't," the lieutenant calms you. "Trust me. I saw the bodies."

fields.Title: Logic: "He's probably right."
fields.Dialogue Text: He's probably right.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Don't beat yourself up about it. I..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Don't beat yourself up about it. I think I gave you a pretty exhaustive answer about those flowers and what they mean."

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "Enough with the goddamn flowers alr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Enough with the goddamn flowers already! Are you a cop or a florist?

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""You mean the guys who were playing..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You mean the guys who were playing pétanque?"

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Home? To work? To get something fro..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Home? To work? To get something from somewhere? Who knows what people are doing when we're not looking.

fields.Title: You: ""Yeah, where did they go?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah, where did they go?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Have you noticed people sometimes..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Have you noticed people sometimes appear and disappear in places? It's called *doing things*."

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "It's very unlikely. Everyone scatte..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's very unlikely. Everyone scattered once the tribunal started. They're probably fine.

fields.Title: You: "Yeah, where did the old guys go?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Yeah, where did the old guys go?

fields.Title: You: ""Right. Let's move." [Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: "Right. Let's move." [Leave.]

fields.Title: You: "That's just how craters are. [Disca..."
fields.Dialogue Text: That's just how craters are. [Discard thought.]

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""You'll get them next time," the li..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You'll get them next time," the lieutenant replies, looking at the empty crater.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "You'll get them next time. But let'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You'll get them next time. But let's be honest, they weren't even in the suspects list.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "You would have wasted *so* much tim..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You would have wasted *so* much time talking to these two pensioners. Precious case-time.
